# 05WT3 – YOLOv8 Fine-Tuning on Protein Secondary Structure Dataset
**Project:** Deep Learning-Based Visual Analytics of Molecular Dynamics Trajectories
**Detection Classes:** alpha_helix (0), beta_sheet (1)
**Week:** 5 | **Task:** 3

---

## Objective

Fine-tune a pretrained YOLOv8 model on the labeled protein trajectory dataset.
Monitor training/validation loss curves to identify the optimal stopping epoch
and prevent overfitting. Save the best weights separately.

---

## Training Script

```python
from ultralytics import YOLO

# Load YOLOv8 nano — pretrained on COCO (transfer learning)
# Nano is fast to train; swap for yolov8s.pt or yolov8m.pt for better accuracy
model = YOLO("yolov8n.pt")

results = model.train(
    data       = "dataset_scaled.yaml",  # protein dataset config
    epochs     = 100,                    # high count to observe full loss curve
    imgsz      = 384,                    # matches our scaled image width
    batch      = 16,                     # reduce to 8 if GPU OOM
    name       = "protein_helix_sheet",  # run folder name
    patience   = 20,                     # early stop if no improvement for 20 epochs
    lr0        = 0.01,                   # initial learning rate
    lrf        = 0.001,                  # final LR (cosine decay)
    momentum   = 0.937,
    weight_decay = 0.0005,
    optimizer  = "AdamW",
    augment    = True,                   # horizontal flip, HSV jitter, mosaic
    hsv_h      = 0.015,                  # hue augmentation (subtle for protein renders)
    hsv_s      = 0.5,
    hsv_v      = 0.3,
    degrees    = 15.0,                   # rotation ±15° — proteins can appear rotated
    fliplr     = 0.5,                    # horizontal flip
    mosaic     = 1.0,                    # mosaic augmentation
    save       = True,
    save_period= 10,                     # checkpoint every 10 epochs
    device     = 0,                      # GPU 0; use 'cpu' if no GPU
    project    = "runs/protein",
    verbose    = True
)
```

